Class Materials

java.lang.Object
cn.nukkit.block.customblock.data.Materials
All Implemented Interfaces:
NBTData
public class Materials extends Object implements NBTData
Used to map the face of the block to the actual material instance and set the rendering method and parameters

    • process

      public void process(@NotNull @NotNull String face, boolean ambientOcclusion, boolean faceDimming, @NotNull @NotNull String renderMethodName, @NotNull @NotNull String texture, @Nullable @Nullable String tintType)
      Specify the corresponding rendering method, rendering parameters and materials.

      This method is completely customized. Please capture the package to confirm the legality of the parameters before using it.

      Parameters:
      face - Specifies the name of the face. The optional value isup, down, north, south, east, west, *
      ambientOcclusion - Should it be applied ambient light shielding when lighting?
      faceDimming - Should it be dimmed according to the direction it is facing?
      renderMethodName - Rendering method to be used
      texture - Specify the texture's name
      tintType - Specify the tinting type
